<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>VP Love Stains - Rules</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <!-- Bootstrap -->
    <link href="../static/bootstrap/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen">
     ${header | n}
  </head>
  <body>
    <script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery.js"></script>
    <script src="../static/bootstrap/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
    <div class ="container">
        <h2>Keepers</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Franchise Player</li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Each team can keep <b>ONE</b> franchise player.</li>
                    <li>Franchise player is kept in round 0. This is the round before the first round.</li>
                    <li>Franchise player can only be kept for one year.</li>
                    <li>Franchise player can be any player, no restrictions based on position drafted previously.</li>
                    <li>Franchise players can be traded during off season. If you don't trade them, they go back into the draft.</li>
                </ul>
            <li>Two additional Keepers</li>
                <ul>
                    <li>In addition to the franchise keeper, you may keep <b>TWO</b> normal keepers.</li>
                    <li>Keepers may not be kept in first three rounds.</li>
                    <li>Keeper position is determined based off of previous years draft.
                        <ul>
                            <li><b>ACCEPTABLE KEEPER:</b> Drafted Jordy Nelson in 6th last year. He would be a 4th this year.</li>
                            <li><b>ACCEPTABLE KEEPER:</b> Drafted Ben Tate in 8th last year. He would be a 6th this year.</li>
                            <li><b>UNACCEPTABLE KEEPER:</b> Drafted Brandon Marshall in 2nd last year. He would only be eligable for franchise status</li>
                            <li><b>UNACCEPTABLE KEEPER:</b> Drafted Danny Amendola in 5th last year. This would mean he would have to be kept in 3rd which you cant do. He would only be eligable for franchise status</li>
                        </ul>
                    <li>Keepers can be kept as long as you can keep them before they get to franchise status.
                    <li>If you picked up a Free Agent last year or someone off waivers. They are kept in last round, plus two. Usually the 14th. </li>
                </ul>
        </ul>

        <h2>Trades</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Trades can be for players or draft picks.</li>
            <li>You may <b>NOT</b> trade for other items or services outside of fantasy football. Example: BJs, Food, etc. These will be rejected.</li>
            <li>You may only trade up until the trade block, and then during the off season.</li>
            <li>The only way a trade will be rejected is if it is pure collusion. You are adults and should know whether your trade is a fair deal or not.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>